From: Chris Liddell <chris.liddell@artifex.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Dec 2021 15:10:12 +0000
Subject: oss-fuzz 42294: Reset buffer length after rewriting xref entry

If we find an invalidly terminated xref entry, we try a slower method to derive
the correct values, and write those back to the buffer with the correct form.

But we were failing to reset the length (which was used as a counter) so the
next block of code could its job.
---
 pdf/pdf_xref.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/pdf/pdf_xref.c b/pdf/pdf_xref.c
index 02ea48054..e777183e9 100644
--- a/pdf/pdf_xref.c
+++ b/pdf/pdf_xref.c
@@ -755,6 +755,7 @@ static int read_xref_section(pdf_context *ctx, pdf_c_stream *s, uint64_t *sectio
                 code = write_offset((byte *)Buffer, off, gen, free);
                 if (code < 0)
                     return code;
+                j = 19;
                 break;
             }
         }
